Reasoning: The paper discusses the simulation of programmable matter systems using self-assembly, which involves the coordination of multiple components to form complex structures. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including multi-agent systems (cs.MA), robotics (cs.RO), distributed systems (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), and control systems (cs.SY). However, given the focus on simulating the behavior of individual components and their interactions, we believe that cs.MA and cs.RO are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.DS, cs.CC, and cs.SY.
